\f2\b\fs24 \cf0 \
Frequently Asked Questions\
\pard\li660\fi-300\ql\qnatural

\fs22 \cf0 Q:
\f1\b0\fs20  Where are my IRC commands?
\f3 \

\f2\b\fs22 A:
\f1\b0\fs20  Colloquy is a simple visual IRC client. If you require IRC commands and Colloquy does not provide suitable options through menus, toolbar icons or current plug-in commands let us know for consideration as a future option or plug-in.\

\f2\b\fs14 \

\fs22 Q:
\f1\b0\fs20  Will Colloquy be AppleScript aware or have an AppleScript plug-in system in the future?
\f3 \

\f2\b\fs22 A:
\f1\b0\fs20  Yes, this is the plan. Currently Colloquy plug-ins need to be written as Cocoa bundles; email timothy@javelin.cc for more information and the plug-in software development kit.
\f3 \

\f2\b\fs14 \

\fs22 Q:
\f1\b0\fs20  Can you add this feature to Colloquy?
\f3 \

\f2\b\fs22 A:
\f1\b0\fs20  Any features or improvement ideas can always be sent to timothy@javelin.cc. We read every suggestion, though someone might not reply back. Providing us examples from existing Mac or Windows products will always help.
\f3 \

\f2\b\fs14 \

\fs22 Q:
\f1\b0\fs20  Will Colloquy continue to be free-ware?
\f3 \

\f2\b\fs22 A:
\f1\b0\fs20  For the time being. Even if Colloquy turns into a shareware product, the price will be in the $5-10 range. Of course, donations can always be sent via PayPal to timothy@javelin.cc. The thought of a "bribe" system is being considered (i.e. put money on features and enhancements you can't live without).
\f3 \
\pard\ql\qnatural

